# No Cursor Co-Author (stack-wide)

Applies to all stack repositories (see `STACK_GIT_REPOS` in `suherman-net-infra/scripts/stack-config.cjs`).

Cursor **automatically injects** `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>` when the agent runs `git commit`, even if the command only uses `-m`. MDC rules alone do not disable this. **`prepare-commit-msg` and `pre-push` hooks enforce removal/blocking** — install with `npm run install-hooks` (this repo) or `npm run install-hooks:stack` from `suherman-net-infra`.

## Required behavior

- Never pass `--trailer`, `--co-authored-by`, or any `Co-authored-by:` line in commit commands or messages.
- Use a **single-line** commit message only: `git commit -m "description"`.
- Do not use multi-line HEREDOC bodies for commits (empty trailing lines can become a body where Cursor adds attribution).
- **After every commit**, verify the result:
  ```bash
  git log -1 --format=%B
  ```
  If the output contains `Co-authored-by`, `cursoragent@cursor.com`, or `Cursor`, immediately fix it:
  ```bash
  GIT_COMMITTER_NAME="Iman Suherman" GIT_COMMITTER_EMAIL="iman.suherman@gmail.com" \
    git commit --amend --author="Iman Suherman <iman.suherman@gmail.com>" -m "same description without co-author"
  ```
  Re-check until the co-author line is gone.

If `git push` is rejected by `pre-push`, amend the flagged commits and push again.

Also disable Cursor attribution in **Cursor Settings > Agent > Attribution** (off).
